OT	Sesame-Peanut Noodles
OT	Serves 4
OT	Serve this colorful noodle dish at room temperature or chilled.
OT	Ingredients
OT	1 (8-ounce) package 100% whole grain soba noodles
OT	2 cups snow peas, strings removed
OT	2 tablespoons roasted, unsalted, unsweetened smooth peanut butter or almond butter
OT	2 tablespoons rice vinegar
OT	1 tablespoon reduced sodium tamari
OT	1 tablespoon sesame tahini
OT	1/8 teaspoon crushed red chile pepper
OT	1 1/2 cups shredded carrots
OT	1 red bell pepper, thinly sliced
OT	1 cup sliced green onions
OT	3 tablespoons toasted sesame seeds
OT	Method
OT	Cook soba noodles according to package directions. Add snow peas with 1 minute cooking time remaining. Drain noodles and snow peas thoroughly.
OT	In a large bowl, whisk together peanut butter, vinegar, tamari, tahini and crushed red pepper. Add a splash of warm water if needed to thin the sauce so it will coat the vegetables and noodles. Add noodles, snow peas, carrots, bell pepper, green onions and sesame seeds. Toss to coat noodles and vegetables thoroughly with sauce. Serve at room temperature or chilled.
